Here's a corrected version of the passage:

The balance between nature and human lifestyle is crucial for protecting the environment, atmosphere, and its various natural resources. Environmental degradation can be disastrous and threaten the very existence of life on earth. Therefore, it is essential to maintain a clean and green environment for a healthy life. The environment directly affects humans and other living beings in several ways. People have adapted to living in certain climatic conditions and have figured out ways to cope with varying climates depending on where they live. Humans are sensitive to their environment, meaning they are used to certain temperatures and changes, but extreme climate changes can affect their working environment and health directly. The environment can also create or reduce stress, which affects us in several ways. Natural processes or human activities such as volcanoes, earthquakes, rainstorms, floods, etc., can directly affect human life.
